  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2007-01-31",
    "date": "2007-02-26T22:00:48Z",
    "text": "Expresses support for the goals and ideals of National Wear Red Day.\n\nEncourages: (1) Americans nationwide to wear red on that day to show support for women's heart disease awareness; (2) all American women to embrace the goals of The Heart Truth campaign and take action to modify, prevent, and control their risk factors for heart disease; and (3) all Americans to exercise regularly and maintain a healthy weight, develop good eating habits, avoid tobacco, drugs, and excessive alcohol, and have regular checkups to take advantage of screenings that can detect heart disease-related problems early.\n\nReaffirms our nation's commitment to fighting heart disease by promoting awareness about its causes, risks, and prevention and by promoting new education programs, supporting research, and expanding access to medical treatment."
  },
